U.S. Army Staf Sgt Julian McDonald welcomed a 4-year-old Belgian Malinois named Layka into his Columbus, Ohio home .
Layka was shot four times at point blank range by an enemy fighter armed with an AK-47 .
McDonald decided to bring Layka home to live with his son Liam .
He has a new family and a medal of honor in recognition of her bravery .